    "lyrics": {
      "text": "When the bod-i-less one was se-cret-ly com-mand---ed, in haste he came__ and stood be-fore__ Jo-seph’s dwell---ing, and spake un-to the Maid-en who knew not wed--lock: The One__ who hath bowed the Heav--ens by His des-cent is held__ and con-tained un-chang--ing whol--ly in thee. See-ing Him tak-ing on the form of a ser-vant in thy womb, I stand in awe and cry to__ thee: Re-joice, thou pure__ and un-wed--ded__ Bride."
    }
